cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for learning bilingual embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of multilingual knowledge bases and random walks also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the Skip-gram model, which is a popular deep learning model for natural language processing, indicating that cs.DL (Deep Learning) could also be a relevant category.
